3 Multi-trait association tests (Chr. 20)

We compared p-values obtained from the following tests.

  • P_phen: the Omnibus test with the covariance matrix estimated from the raw phenotype data (the correlation matrix among phenotypes);
  • P_ldsc: the Omnibus test with the covariance matrix by LDSC;
  • P_ldsc_sc: the Omnibus test with the covariance matrix by LDSC and further scale by cov2cor function;

Note that P_phen seem to be in a good concordance with MANOVA (see the next section), which in turn well approximates the PLINK-CCA test.

Analysis is performed on SNPs from Chr. 20.
